.SH Name
.SP 5 5
pretty_short -  This method does weird stuff.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
varargs string pretty_short(object thing)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^thing%^RESET%^ - the viewer
.EI

.SH Returns
.SI 5
the string being the short
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/basic/desc.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This method does weird stuff.  Pretty much it just calls the
short() function with the dark parameter...  This should not be
used to generate output.  Use a_short(), the_short(), or
one_short or poss_short() instead.
.EP

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
short(), /global/player->check_dark(), a_short(), the_short(), poss_short(), one_short()

.EP

